{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1000/comments/1408665.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/gazebo/diff/osrf/gazebo:9b7492d4aa21..e01a9d50cbf7?path=tools%2Fwebsite%2Fgazebo_install.run"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1000/_/diff#comment-1408665"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 1000, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/1000.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/1000"}}, "title": "Scripts for the new gazebo website"}, "content": {"raw": "The old school bash boys used to say: eval is evil. We can play with some escapes and probably something like this:\n\n```\n#!bash\nsudo sh -c \"echo \\\"deb http://packages.osrfoundation.org/gazebo/ubuntu ${codename} main\\\" > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/gazebo_install-latest.list\"\n```\n\nshould work and avoid the use of eval.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>The old school bash boys used to say: eval is evil. We can play with some escapes and probably something like this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-bash\"><pre><span></span>sudo sh -c <span class=\"s2\">&quot;echo \\&quot;deb http://packages.osrfoundation.org/gazebo/ubuntu </span><span class=\"si\">${</span><span class=\"nv\">codename</span><span class=\"si\">}</span><span class=\"s2\"> main\\&quot; &gt; /etc/apt/sources.list.d/gazebo_install-latest.list&quot;</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>should work and avoid the use of eval.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2014-03-12T16:25:37.694497+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Jose Luis Rivero", "uuid": "{d12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/109284c8b83411dbc7492138f6167e9ed=httpsavatar-managemen